1
00:00:00,750 --> 00:00:03,128
[tense music playing]

2
00:00:04,671 --> 00:00:06,589
- [music intensifies]
- [blade slashes]

3
00:00:07,882 --> 00:00:08,925
[Jalil] <i>In war,</i>

4
00:00:09,676 --> 00:00:12,303
<i>it's easy to know who's on your side,</i>

5
00:00:12,387 --> 00:00:15,348
- [grunting, groaning]
- <i>who the enemy is…</i>

6
00:00:15,432 --> 00:00:17,517
[groans in pain]

7
00:00:17,600 --> 00:00:20,895
[Jalil] <i>…and who</i>
<i>you're supposed to be afraid of.</i>

8
00:00:21,813 --> 00:00:23,773
- [Jalil] <i>Remember!</i>
- [clapping]

9
00:00:23,857 --> 00:00:27,068
<i>You're not learning how to fight</i>
<i>because you want trouble,</i>

10
00:00:27,152 --> 00:00:31,322
<i>but because you want to keep the peace</i>

11
00:00:31,406 --> 00:00:33,450
<i>and harmony in your homes</i>

12
00:00:33,533 --> 00:00:36,661
<i>as members of the CPSU.</i>

13
00:00:37,162 --> 00:00:40,457
[Jalil] <i>But what if everyone has a gun?</i>

14
00:00:41,458 --> 00:00:43,251
<i>Guns that are held by the wrong people?</i>

15
00:00:43,334 --> 00:00:44,586
[guns cocking]

16
00:00:44,669 --> 00:00:48,006
<i>People who are driven</i>
<i>by fear and violence.</i>

17
00:00:48,965 --> 00:00:51,384
[Jalil] There's no need to shoot.

18
00:00:51,968 --> 00:00:53,970
There's no need for a bloodbath.

19
00:00:54,054 --> 00:00:55,597
Just leave now

20
00:00:55,680 --> 00:00:57,182
and never come back.

21
00:00:57,265 --> 00:00:58,892
[music intensifies]

22
00:01:02,187 --> 00:01:03,980
[masked men] Let's go! Hurry!

23
00:01:09,402 --> 00:01:11,279
[Jalil] <i>We are fighting to stop this.</i>

24
00:01:12,322 --> 00:01:15,617
<i>To keep the chaos away</i>
<i>from our communities and our homes.</i>

25
00:01:18,703 --> 00:01:20,038
- [gunshot]
- [grunts]

26
00:01:20,121 --> 00:01:21,915
[gunfire]

27
00:01:25,168 --> 00:01:26,544
[Jalil] Surrender yourself!

28
00:01:26,628 --> 00:01:29,255
Do you really think you can stop us?

29
00:01:29,339 --> 00:01:32,634
- [tense music]
- We're bigger than you think!

30
00:01:32,717 --> 00:01:33,676
You're helpless!

31
00:01:33,760 --> 00:01:35,929
You have never seen a war like this!

32
00:01:36,012 --> 00:01:38,556
[gunfire]

33
00:01:40,558 --> 00:01:43,937
[tense music playing]

34
00:01:45,855 --> 00:01:48,066
[Jalil] <i>But is what we're doing enough?</i>

35
00:01:48,775 --> 00:01:52,195
<i>Or is the opponent</i>
<i>too strong to be stopped?</i>

36
00:01:54,405 --> 00:01:57,117
<i>What's even more terrifying</i>
<i>than the gunfire noise</i>

37
00:01:58,201 --> 00:02:01,412
<i>is the silence after the chaos.</i>

38
00:02:01,496 --> 00:02:03,790
[grim music plays]

39
00:02:11,005 --> 00:02:13,925
[mysterious theme music playing]

40
00:02:30,859 --> 00:02:33,570
- [upbeat feel-good music playing]
- [critters chirping]

41
00:02:34,863 --> 00:02:37,073
[people talking indistinctly]

42
00:02:49,919 --> 00:02:51,337
Jamilah, dear.

43
00:02:51,421 --> 00:02:53,798
You look so deep in thought.

44
00:02:53,882 --> 00:02:56,134
Thinking about your brother again?

45
00:02:56,885 --> 00:02:58,928
- [melancholic music]
- [sighs, clicks tongue]

46
00:02:59,012 --> 00:03:01,139
Yes, Aunt Aminah.

47
00:03:01,848 --> 00:03:05,184
You know what? I miss Jalil so much.

48
00:03:06,352 --> 00:03:09,105
He's been in Basilan for three months

49
00:03:09,188 --> 00:03:12,108
to train the new members

50
00:03:12,191 --> 00:03:14,527
of the Civilian Defense Service Unit.

51
00:03:14,611 --> 00:03:19,741
You know he's one
of our best fighters here.

52
00:03:19,824 --> 00:03:21,868
That's why he always gets to train men

53
00:03:21,951 --> 00:03:25,455
who want to protect their community.

54
00:03:25,538 --> 00:03:27,540
Just like us here. See?

55
00:03:27,624 --> 00:03:29,667
Everyone is so happy.

56
00:03:29,751 --> 00:03:32,921
No one will dare ruin our peace.

57
00:03:33,004 --> 00:03:35,757
And that's because
of your father and your brother.

58
00:03:38,134 --> 00:03:41,512
[clicks tongue, sighs] But how about you?

59
00:03:41,596 --> 00:03:44,515
Don't you want to go back to the city

60
00:03:44,599 --> 00:03:48,436
to fulfill your nurse duties?

61
00:03:49,187 --> 00:03:51,606
- No, Auntie.
- Hmm.

62
00:03:51,689 --> 00:03:53,107
I'd rather stay here.

63
00:03:53,691 --> 00:03:56,486
Besides, I like it better here.

64
00:03:57,362 --> 00:03:58,446
Just look at them.

65
00:04:00,156 --> 00:04:01,449
[Jamilah] They look so happy.

66
00:04:02,283 --> 00:04:04,577
The air here is fresh,

67
00:04:05,828 --> 00:04:06,704
relaxing.

68
00:04:07,413 --> 00:04:09,958
We're all family here.

69
00:04:11,084 --> 00:04:12,627
And most of all…

70
00:04:14,254 --> 00:04:15,255
it's peaceful.

71
00:04:16,297 --> 00:04:18,633
Datu Rahman's arrest will be a huge help

72
00:04:18,716 --> 00:04:20,009
to our investigation.

73
00:04:21,678 --> 00:04:23,596
That's why we need to succeed, Lara.

74
00:04:23,680 --> 00:04:24,514
Mm-hmm.

75
00:04:24,597 --> 00:04:26,641
You should be careful, Marcus.

76
00:04:26,724 --> 00:04:27,976
[gentle music]

77
00:04:28,059 --> 00:04:30,687
We're just getting started
with the Task Force Alpha mission,

78
00:04:30,770 --> 00:04:33,231
and we're already dealing
with prominent people.

79
00:04:33,314 --> 00:04:35,608
They'd all celebrate if it means you die.

80
00:04:35,692 --> 00:04:37,819
[scoffs] You know what, Lara?

81
00:04:38,319 --> 00:04:40,488
If a criminal isn't mad at me,

82
00:04:40,571 --> 00:04:42,448
that means I'm not doing my job right.

83
00:04:42,532 --> 00:04:45,910
[chuckles] Okay, then, Mr. Unbothered.

84
00:04:45,994 --> 00:04:47,704
Alright. Take care, Agent Reyes.

85
00:04:48,204 --> 00:04:49,664
Yes, ma'am.

86
00:04:50,748 --> 00:04:51,958
[chuckles]

87
00:04:53,960 --> 00:04:57,005
[pensive music playing]

88
00:05:13,229 --> 00:05:19,861
[pensive music continues]

89
00:05:30,204 --> 00:05:31,664
Don't worry, boss.

90
00:05:31,748 --> 00:05:33,333
I'll take care of Marcus.

91
00:05:34,125 --> 00:05:35,418
Consider it done.

92
00:05:35,501 --> 00:05:38,171
[unsettling music playing]

93
00:06:05,073 --> 00:06:07,200
You still got
your family's photo with you?

94
00:06:08,076 --> 00:06:09,202
Yes, sir.

95
00:06:09,994 --> 00:06:10,912
Always.

96
00:06:12,121 --> 00:06:14,957
It's to remind myself to take care

97
00:06:15,041 --> 00:06:17,293
and come home to them after this.

98
00:06:18,252 --> 00:06:20,088
You're just like Rustia.

99
00:06:20,588 --> 00:06:21,839
But his family is a dog.

100
00:06:21,923 --> 00:06:22,757
[men chuckle]

101
00:06:22,840 --> 00:06:26,302
Coochie isn't just a dog, okay?

102
00:06:26,803 --> 00:06:29,305
- He's more than family to me!
- Yeah, yeah.

103
00:06:29,388 --> 00:06:30,807
Look, he's so cute!

104
00:06:34,102 --> 00:06:35,978
[Russel] Oh, I don't care
about your plans.

105
00:06:36,062 --> 00:06:37,730
But when I get home,

106
00:06:37,814 --> 00:06:39,649
I'm going to propose to my girlfriend.

107
00:06:39,732 --> 00:06:41,192
- I want to get married.
- Wow. Great!

108
00:06:41,275 --> 00:06:43,236
- That's cool, man.
- Congrats.

109
00:06:43,319 --> 00:06:44,362
- [man 1] Adulting!
- [man 2] Yeah.

110
00:06:44,445 --> 00:06:47,406
How about you, Suarez?
Don't you want to get married?

111
00:06:47,490 --> 00:06:48,491
Not yet.

112
00:06:48,991 --> 00:06:51,619
Not until I finish building
my parents' home.

113
00:06:51,702 --> 00:06:52,995
Oh, me, too!

114
00:06:53,496 --> 00:06:55,456
I can finally get married now

115
00:06:55,540 --> 00:06:57,625
since my brother just completed
his Civil Engineering course.

116
00:06:57,708 --> 00:06:58,584
[men] Wow!

117
00:06:58,668 --> 00:06:59,627
[man 3] Congrats, man!

118
00:06:59,710 --> 00:07:01,254
- That's awesome.
- That great.

119
00:07:01,337 --> 00:07:02,171
What about you, Domingo?

120
00:07:02,255 --> 00:07:04,632
What's your plan when we get back?

121
00:07:07,760 --> 00:07:08,594
This.

122
00:07:09,470 --> 00:07:11,597
Work, work, work.

123
00:07:11,681 --> 00:07:13,349
- Wow!
- Just work?

124
00:07:13,433 --> 00:07:15,685
Domingo's really hardworking!

125
00:07:15,768 --> 00:07:17,061
- Oh.
- Idol!

126
00:07:17,145 --> 00:07:19,439
- [chuckling]
- Employee of the month!

127
00:07:19,522 --> 00:07:20,523
- [man 1 chuckles]
- [man 2] Hey!

128
00:07:20,606 --> 00:07:22,358
- [man 2] Workaholic!
- You guys are crazy.

129
00:07:22,442 --> 00:07:23,651
[men laughing]

130
00:07:23,734 --> 00:07:26,195
You're just trying to get
a good shot with Lara.

131
00:07:26,279 --> 00:07:28,781
[laughing]

132
00:07:28,865 --> 00:07:30,700
Ah, right, sorry, that was for Marcus.

133
00:07:30,783 --> 00:07:32,243
Whoa!

134
00:07:32,326 --> 00:07:34,912
- [chuckling]
- Ooh!

135
00:07:34,996 --> 00:07:37,081
[ominous music playing]

136
00:07:59,103 --> 00:08:01,814
[ominous music continues]

137
00:08:19,916 --> 00:08:21,792
[ominous music continues]

138
00:08:43,064 --> 00:08:46,150
- [ominous music continues]
- [helicopter whirring]

139
00:09:09,966 --> 00:09:12,885
[ominous music continues]

140
00:09:21,477 --> 00:09:22,812
[Jalil] Peace be upon you.

141
00:09:22,895 --> 00:09:25,231
Jalil, we're so glad you're back.

142
00:09:25,314 --> 00:09:27,108
- [man] How are you?
- [Jamilah] Jalil!

143
00:09:27,191 --> 00:09:28,776
- [Jalil] Jamilah!
- [Jamilah chuckles]

144
00:09:29,860 --> 00:09:30,736
[Jalil] Jamilah!

145
00:09:30,820 --> 00:09:32,238
[Jamilah] Jalil!

146
00:09:32,947 --> 00:09:34,240
You've been gone such a long time.

147
00:09:34,323 --> 00:09:36,158
- [man 1] Jalil!
- [man 2] Peace be upon you.

148
00:09:36,242 --> 00:09:40,871
[Jalil] I was only gone three months
to train new CDSU members.

149
00:09:41,872 --> 00:09:44,375
- [woman] Hi, Jalil!
- You'd think I'd been gone ten years.

150
00:09:45,668 --> 00:09:48,254
Of course, Father and I missed you.

151
00:09:48,337 --> 00:09:50,506
- [Jamilah] And…
- [woman] Welcome back, Jalil!

152
00:09:50,590 --> 00:09:54,302
Look, our neighbors
have been waiting for you too.

153
00:09:55,636 --> 00:09:56,470
Jamilah.

154
00:09:58,681 --> 00:10:00,516
Dear, this is my home.

155
00:10:00,600 --> 00:10:02,310
And you're my family.

156
00:10:02,977 --> 00:10:07,982
No matter what happens,
I'll always come back here.

157
00:10:09,191 --> 00:10:10,318
Okay?

158
00:10:10,401 --> 00:10:11,944
[chuckles]

159
00:10:12,862 --> 00:10:14,697
[man] Peace be upon you, Jalil.

160
00:10:14,780 --> 00:10:15,656
And peace be upon you too!

161
00:10:15,740 --> 00:10:18,242
- Peace be upon you.
- How are you?

162
00:10:18,993 --> 00:10:20,286
Jalil, come here, son.

163
00:10:21,912 --> 00:10:23,039
Father.

164
00:10:24,373 --> 00:10:25,124
Mm.

165
00:10:25,207 --> 00:10:27,585
[gentle music playing]

166
00:10:28,169 --> 00:10:29,920
[father] I'm glad you arrived safely.

167
00:10:30,004 --> 00:10:32,340
I have something to show you.

168
00:10:32,965 --> 00:10:34,592
[father groans]

169
00:10:36,260 --> 00:10:39,096
[tense music playing]

170
00:10:41,849 --> 00:10:44,935
[ominous music playing]

171
00:10:45,978 --> 00:10:49,023
[helicopter whirring]

172
00:10:55,863 --> 00:10:58,866
[ominous music continues]

173
00:11:05,873 --> 00:11:08,167
Command, this is Alpha One.

174
00:11:15,800 --> 00:11:18,427
Approaching landing zone in 30 seconds.

175
00:11:19,470 --> 00:11:22,264
Copy, Alpha One, perimeter is clear.
Proceed with the drop.

176
00:11:24,100 --> 00:11:25,267
Roger.

177
00:11:25,768 --> 00:11:28,771
[ominous music continues]

178
00:11:49,667 --> 00:11:50,918
Team, get ready!

179
00:11:51,001 --> 00:11:52,586
Draft and loaded, let's go!

180
00:11:52,670 --> 00:11:54,130
- Roger!
- Roger!

181
00:11:54,797 --> 00:11:56,674
- Whoo!
- Let's do this!

182
00:12:01,178 --> 00:12:04,473
[helicopter whirring]

183
00:12:04,557 --> 00:12:07,685
Copy, maintain overwatch
and update on movement.

184
00:12:11,105 --> 00:12:13,899
[unsettling music playing]

185
00:12:17,903 --> 00:12:18,988
[man] There.

186
00:12:20,448 --> 00:12:22,783
[unsettling music playing]

187
00:12:22,867 --> 00:12:24,076
It's full.

188
00:12:25,202 --> 00:12:26,829
We've got nowhere else to put it.

189
00:12:26,912 --> 00:12:31,375
The syndicate hasn't stopped
dumping weapons

190
00:12:31,459 --> 00:12:32,918
in the sea near us.

191
00:12:33,711 --> 00:12:36,630
We need to turn these over to the police.

192
00:12:37,840 --> 00:12:39,341
We can't!

193
00:12:40,843 --> 00:12:44,972
We don't know who we can trust
in the police.

194
00:12:46,557 --> 00:12:48,559
What if the syndicate pays them off?

195
00:12:49,643 --> 00:12:52,938
Those weapons will end up
in the wrong hands.

196
00:12:53,647 --> 00:12:57,359
What if we use them to protect
our village from criminals?

197
00:12:57,443 --> 00:12:58,569
[Jalil] We can't.

198
00:12:59,361 --> 00:13:00,988
We'd be pinned down.

199
00:13:01,071 --> 00:13:05,034
But this is a good chance
to fight the criminals

200
00:13:05,117 --> 00:13:07,244
who abuse and exploit us.

201
00:13:08,204 --> 00:13:11,248
Recently, the women of Rio Hermoso

202
00:13:11,332 --> 00:13:13,334
were kidnapped and sold.

203
00:13:13,417 --> 00:13:16,086
Are we just going to let that
happen in our town?

204
00:13:16,170 --> 00:13:18,088
What if they invade us?

205
00:13:18,172 --> 00:13:20,799
There are other ways to fight them.

206
00:13:21,509 --> 00:13:22,968
These weapons…

207
00:13:23,052 --> 00:13:26,388
We'll bury these and forget.

208
00:13:32,144 --> 00:13:33,479
If God wills.

209
00:13:33,562 --> 00:13:36,565
[tense music playing]

210
00:13:42,321 --> 00:13:45,366
[boat engine roaring]

211
00:13:45,449 --> 00:13:48,202
[sinister music playing]

212
00:13:53,958 --> 00:13:56,043
Tomorrow, as soon as the sun rises,

213
00:13:56,126 --> 00:14:00,089
dig somewhere in the woods,
and bury those weapons.

214
00:14:00,589 --> 00:14:01,757
Yes, Datu.

215
00:14:03,217 --> 00:14:04,218
[Rahman sighs]

216
00:14:07,429 --> 00:14:10,099
[boat engine roaring]

217
00:14:28,033 --> 00:14:29,285
[Jamilah] Thank you!

218
00:14:31,287 --> 00:14:33,080
[man] Ah, Jamilah, Jamilah! Wait!

219
00:14:33,163 --> 00:14:36,125
- [Jamilah] Hm?
- Will your brother stay here?

220
00:14:36,917 --> 00:14:39,044
Yes. That's also what he wants.

221
00:14:39,128 --> 00:14:42,464
[stirring music playing]

222
00:14:48,762 --> 00:14:52,558
Your brother is really my idol.
I hope he trains us again.

223
00:14:52,641 --> 00:14:54,393
Our moves might get rusty.

224
00:14:54,476 --> 00:14:57,354
You know, you better fix
that net of yours.

225
00:14:59,398 --> 00:15:02,276
[stirring music continues]

226
00:15:10,534 --> 00:15:13,495
[low buzzing]

227
00:15:14,788 --> 00:15:17,750
[suspenseful music playing]

228
00:15:37,645 --> 00:15:38,896
Stop.

229
00:15:39,939 --> 00:15:43,317
[suspenseful music continues]

230
00:16:01,585 --> 00:16:05,214
[suspenseful music continues]

231
00:16:28,028 --> 00:16:29,238
Team Alpha to base.

232
00:16:29,321 --> 00:16:31,281
[system beeping]

233
00:16:31,365 --> 00:16:33,993
- [Lara] This is base.
- Visual confirmation of Datu Rahman.

234
00:16:34,076 --> 00:16:34,910
[Lara] <i>Copy.</i>

235
00:16:37,162 --> 00:16:40,165
[suspenseful music continues]

236
00:16:48,757 --> 00:16:49,842
Move out.

237
00:16:50,759 --> 00:16:53,846
[leaves rustling]

238
00:16:55,347 --> 00:16:58,350
[sinister music playing]

239
00:17:18,996 --> 00:17:21,999
[ominous music playing]

240
00:17:27,421 --> 00:17:30,507
[rustling]

241
00:17:33,302 --> 00:17:35,262
Sir, why? Is there a problem?

242
00:17:40,809 --> 00:17:42,728
[footsteps]

243
00:17:43,729 --> 00:17:44,772
Something's wrong.

244
00:17:44,855 --> 00:17:49,068
[ominous music continues]

245
00:17:49,151 --> 00:17:50,652
The area's full of civilians.

246
00:17:51,153 --> 00:17:53,363
Still, be careful. Looks can be deceiving.

247
00:17:54,531 --> 00:17:56,116
[system beeping]

248
00:18:00,829 --> 00:18:02,748
- [woman, indistinctly]
- [overlapping chatter]

249
00:18:05,667 --> 00:18:07,336
[footsteps]

250
00:18:08,837 --> 00:18:10,923
[leaves rustling]

251
00:18:11,006 --> 00:18:13,759
- [indistinct chattering]
- [woman laughing]

252
00:18:13,842 --> 00:18:15,552
[players] The odd one is it!

253
00:18:15,636 --> 00:18:18,680
- [child 1] You're it!
- [child 2] Me?! Me?

254
00:18:18,764 --> 00:18:20,015
[woman] Okay, but you first!

255
00:18:20,099 --> 00:18:21,225
Let's eat.

256
00:18:24,269 --> 00:18:25,729
[man] <i>Neutralize the area!</i>

257
00:18:25,813 --> 00:18:28,107
<i>There are no civilians there!</i>
<i>They'll ambush you!</i>

258
00:18:28,190 --> 00:18:29,399
[radio crackles]

259
00:18:30,526 --> 00:18:31,777
- [radio beeps]
- [Marcus] Negative.

260
00:18:31,860 --> 00:18:33,195
The area is full of civilians.

261
00:18:33,278 --> 00:18:34,822
I repeat, the area is full of civilians.

262
00:18:37,282 --> 00:18:39,284
Team, hold your fire.

263
00:18:40,160 --> 00:18:42,412
Hold your fire. No one shoots.

264
00:18:47,626 --> 00:18:50,963
[ominous music playing]

265
00:18:51,046 --> 00:18:53,757
[indistinct chatter]

266
00:19:01,682 --> 00:19:04,685
[ominous music continues]

267
00:19:09,606 --> 00:19:11,483
- [gunshot]
- [Marcus grunts]

268
00:19:13,652 --> 00:19:14,862
Marcus?

269
00:19:16,488 --> 00:19:18,949
- Where'd that come from?!
- [soldier] Sir! What are we going to do?

270
00:19:19,825 --> 00:19:20,909
Hold your fire!

271
00:19:20,993 --> 00:19:24,079
[tense music playing]

272
00:19:33,297 --> 00:19:34,882
[man] What was that?

273
00:19:35,465 --> 00:19:37,342
[screen crackling]

274
00:19:38,135 --> 00:19:41,054
[tense music continues]

275
00:19:43,515 --> 00:19:45,517
[indistinct chattering]

276
00:19:50,063 --> 00:19:52,191
- [gunshots]
- [screaming]

277
00:19:53,275 --> 00:19:55,527
- Jalil!
- Run!

278
00:19:55,611 --> 00:19:58,155
[people screaming]

279
00:19:58,238 --> 00:19:59,531
[people shouting]

280
00:20:00,574 --> 00:20:03,035
[rapid gunfire]

281
00:20:03,118 --> 00:20:07,164
- [people screaming]
- [gunshots]

282
00:20:07,247 --> 00:20:08,790
Help!

283
00:20:09,499 --> 00:20:10,417
- [Jamilah] Go, run!
- [people shouting]

284
00:20:14,087 --> 00:20:17,382
[gunshots]

285
00:20:17,466 --> 00:20:18,759
Father!

286
00:20:19,509 --> 00:20:21,011
Father! Jamilah!

287
00:20:22,721 --> 00:20:24,389
[rapid gunfire]

288
00:20:24,473 --> 00:20:26,516
Agent Reyes, do you hear me?

289
00:20:26,600 --> 00:20:29,311
- [gunshots]
- Argh!

290
00:20:29,978 --> 00:20:31,939
They're raining bullets on us, sir!

291
00:20:32,022 --> 00:20:34,608
[people screaming]

292
00:20:35,651 --> 00:20:38,946
[gunshots]

293
00:20:39,655 --> 00:20:40,530
[woman whimpers]

294
00:20:40,614 --> 00:20:42,574
Stand! Quick! Stand!

295
00:20:43,450 --> 00:20:44,576
Stay inside.

296
00:20:44,660 --> 00:20:47,496
[gunshots blasting]

297
00:20:48,914 --> 00:20:50,415
Help! Help!

298
00:20:50,499 --> 00:20:52,751
- [gunshots blasting]
- [people shouting]

299
00:20:55,671 --> 00:20:57,965
- [soldier 1] This is an ambush!
- [soldier 2] Hold your fire!

300
00:20:59,049 --> 00:21:01,009
Why are you doing this?!

301
00:21:01,760 --> 00:21:03,887
We are not your enemy!

302
00:21:04,680 --> 00:21:06,390
- [gunshots blasting]
- Oh.

303
00:21:11,979 --> 00:21:14,731
Why?! Why?!

304
00:21:14,815 --> 00:21:15,941
What are you doing?!

305
00:21:16,650 --> 00:21:19,444
Argh! A lot of innocent people
will die from what you're doing!

306
00:21:20,445 --> 00:21:21,947
We will fight!

307
00:21:23,115 --> 00:21:25,742
We will fight back!

308
00:21:27,077 --> 00:21:30,539
- We will fight back!
- Father! Father!

309
00:21:30,622 --> 00:21:32,874
Sir, this is war!

310
00:21:32,958 --> 00:21:35,377
They're going to kill us!
Do you want to die?!

311
00:21:35,460 --> 00:21:37,087
[Jalil] No! Leave those alone!

312
00:21:37,170 --> 00:21:40,590
- Father, no!
- We have to defend ourselves!

313
00:21:40,674 --> 00:21:43,010
[overlapping screams]

314
00:21:43,593 --> 00:21:45,429
- [grunts]
- [Marcus] Domingo!

315
00:21:45,512 --> 00:21:47,347
- No!
- Get out of the way!

316
00:21:47,431 --> 00:21:48,640
Wait!

317
00:21:48,724 --> 00:21:50,434
- They're shooting at us!
- Domingo!

318
00:21:50,517 --> 00:21:52,269
- God is great!
- Father!

319
00:21:54,313 --> 00:21:55,147
Domingo!

320
00:21:56,315 --> 00:21:58,150
- Father, no!
- No!

321
00:22:02,612 --> 00:22:04,823
- [gunshots blasting]
- [Jalil] Father!

322
00:22:04,906 --> 00:22:07,743
- [gunshots blasting]
- [woman] Allah!

323
00:22:07,826 --> 00:22:10,078
- [father] Put that down!
- [Jalil] Father, don't do this.

324
00:22:10,162 --> 00:22:13,457
Dear, we have to defend ourselves!

325
00:22:13,540 --> 00:22:14,333
What did you do?

326
00:22:15,042 --> 00:22:15,959
[grunts]

327
00:22:16,043 --> 00:22:17,836
Innocent lives will be involved
because of what you're doing!

328
00:22:17,919 --> 00:22:19,171
This is war!

329
00:22:19,254 --> 00:22:22,466
[gunshots blasting]

330
00:22:26,386 --> 00:22:27,888
[fire blazing]

331
00:22:27,971 --> 00:22:30,891
- [people clamoring]
- [gunshots blasting]

332
00:22:30,974 --> 00:22:32,768
The mission is compromised.

333
00:22:32,851 --> 00:22:34,269
This can't happen! This can't happen!

334
00:22:34,352 --> 00:22:36,480
[Lara] <i>We need to help Marcus!</i>

335
00:22:36,563 --> 00:22:40,442
As we speak, they are being butchered
and they are so severely outnumbered.

336
00:22:40,525 --> 00:22:43,612
Even if we send a backup there,
I doubt they'd make it.

337
00:22:43,695 --> 00:22:45,155
[gunshots blasting]

338
00:22:45,238 --> 00:22:47,407
God is great!

339
00:22:47,491 --> 00:22:48,450
Datu Rahman spotted.

340
00:22:49,326 --> 00:22:50,952
[shouting]

341
00:22:51,036 --> 00:22:53,371
[Jalil] <i>We were living in peace!</i>

342
00:22:53,455 --> 00:22:55,082
<i>But you keep taking that away from us!</i>

343
00:22:55,165 --> 00:22:56,458
[both grunt]
